switch (member.kind()) {
        case METHOD:
          checkMethod(classTree, (MethodTree) member);
          break;
        case VARIABLE:
          checkVariable(classTree, (VariableTree) member);
          break;
        case CONSTRUCTOR: ...
        case CLASS: ...
        case INTERFACE: ...

      }

To my mind it will be more readable, too many else if is quite difficult to understand

